FAQ

Q: Can I use this for personal wallet backup?
A: Yes. Personal, non-commercial use is free.

Q: Can I audit the code for security?
A: Yes. Security research and auditing is expressly permitted.

Q: Can I fork this and run my own instance?
A: Yes, for non-commercial purposes. If you want to run it as a business,
   you need a Commercial License.

Q: What happens in 2030?
A: The code becomes AGPL v3.0, which is fully open source but requires
   derivative works to also be open source.

Q: Can I use this in my startup?
A: If your startup generates revenue (or intends to), you need a Commercial
   License. If you're pre-revenue and just evaluating, you're fine.

